---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="A Day with me at FunGab Global Studio in Northumbria — Blog" description="Experience a behind-the-scenes look at our creative studio in Northumbria">
  <!-- Article Header -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[50vh] w-full text-white pt-32 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <img 
      src="/blog/blog-1.png" 
      alt="A Day at the Studio" 
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-black/80 via-black/70 to-black/50"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-16 pt-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-[#D234C7]/20 text-[#D234C7] rounded-full">
          News & Updates
        </span>
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">January 11, 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">A Day with me at FunGab Global Studio in Northumbria</h1>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-200">
        <span>By FunGab Team</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article Content -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 md:px-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Welcome to an exclusive behind-the-scenes tour of FunGab Global Studio, nestled in the heart of Northumbria. Today, we're giving you an intimate look at what happens when creativity meets technical excellence.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Morning Preparations</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Every great recording session starts hours before the artists arrive. Our morning routine involves comprehensive equipment checks, acoustic verification, and software calibration. Our team ensures that every microphone is positioned perfectly, every cable is tested, and every monitoring system is operating at peak performance.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The studio's acoustic design is something we're incredibly proud of. Over the years, we've invested in premium sound treatment materials and architectural modifications that transform raw space into a sonic masterpiece. The control room features a perfectly calibrated monitoring environment with reference-grade speakers positioned to create an ideal listening sweet spot.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">The Recording Process</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        When our artists arrive, the magic begins. We start with a technical soundcheck, allowing performers to familiarize themselves with the microphone positioning and monitoring setup. This is crucial—comfort breeds confidence, and confidence produces incredible performances.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Our recording engineer, Marcus, guides each session with meticulous attention to detail. From microphone selection to compression settings, every parameter is optimized for the artist's unique voice and the project's sonic vision. We typically record multiple takes, giving artists the freedom to experiment while capturing various interpretations of the song.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Mixing and Post-Production</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        After recording wraps, the real work begins. Our mixing engineer takes the raw recordings and shapes them into polished, professional-sounding tracks. This involves careful balance of vocals and instruments, strategic use of EQ and compression, and spatial processing to create depth and dimension.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        We pride ourselves on our mixing philosophy: enhancing without overwhelming, refining without losing the artist's authentic voice. Every decision is purposeful, every effect is earned. We spend hours on each mix, taking breaks to refresh our ears and ensure objective decision-making.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Quality Control and Mastering</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Before a track is finalized, it goes through rigorous quality control. We A/B test against commercial reference tracks, verify the mix on multiple playback systems (studio monitors, headphones, car audio, phone speakers), and make meticulous adjustments.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Finally, our mastering engineer adds the finishing polish, optimizing the mix for all playback platforms while maintaining the artistic intent. This final stage is where science and art meet, transforming great mixes into professional releases that translate perfectly across all mediums.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Why FunGab Global?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        What sets FunGab Global apart is our commitment to excellence combined with our genuine passion for music. We're not just recording tracks—we're capturing artistic vision. Every member of our team brings decades of combined experience and an unwavering dedication to quality.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Whether you're an emerging artist looking for your breakout recording or an established professional seeking world-class production, FunGab Global is ready to bring your vision to life. Our studio doors are always open to extraordinary talent and creative ambition.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Author Info -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-[#D234C7] to-[#32BEF1]"></div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">FunGab Team</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Creative professionals dedicated to delivering exceptional music production and creative services.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-12 pt-12 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-[#D234C7] font-semibold hover:underline">← Back to Blog</a>
        <a href="/blog/find-your-unique-voice" class="text-[#D234C7] font-semibold hover:underline">Next Article →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Posts -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 md:px-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-gray-900">More from Our Blog</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <a href="/blog/find-your-unique-voice" class="group bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="h-48 overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/blog/blog-2.png" alt="Find Your Unique Voice" class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 group-hover:text-[#D234C7]">How to Find Your Own Unique Voice?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">November 16, 2025 • 8 min read</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/when-to-start-singing" class="group bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="h-48 overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/blog/blog-3.png" alt="When to Start Singing" class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 group-hover:text-[#D234C7]">When Should I Start Singing Songs?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">December 13, 2024 • 6 min read</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/music-production-guide" class="group bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="h-48 overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/assets/services/music.png" alt="Music Production Guide" class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 group-hover:text-[#D234C7]">The Complete Guide to Modern Music Production</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">January 5, 2026 • 12 min read</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
